Cape Town - The Western Cape Rehabilitation Centre in Lentegeur is one of a kind and is the biggest state funded supplier of prosthetic legs in the province. The centre has been operating for the last 10 years and has brought the gift of walking to approximately 150 000 patients. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
